[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       globals()["fetch_patient_state"] = mock_fetch
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       # ... demo code ...
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   finally:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       globals()["fetch_patient_state"] = fetch_patient_state_backup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   Or better for teaching: pass `fetch_patient_state` as a parameter to `generate_treatment_recommendation` with a default, avoiding monkey-patching entirely.
